<description>Chatterino is a chat client for Twitch chat. It aims to be an improved/extended version of the Twitch web chat.</description>
<summary>Chatterino is a chat client for Twitch.tv</summary>
<releaseNotes>
## Fortnightly
- Minor: Remove TwitchEmotes.com attribution and the open/copy options when right-clicking a Twitch Emote.
- Minor: Strip leading @ and trailing , from username in /user and /usercard commands.
- Minor: Display a system message when reloading subscription emotes to match BTTV/FFZ behavior.
- Minor: Allow resub messages to show in `/mentions` tab.
- Minor: Added a setting to hide similar messages by any user.
- Minor: Duplicate spaces now count towards the display message length.
- Minor: Commands are now backed up.
- Minor: Added the ability to open an entire tab as a popup.
- Minor: Added optional parameter to `/usercard` command for opening a usercard in a different channel context.
- Minor: Added regex option to Nicknames.
- Bugfix: Fixed colored usernames sometimes not working.
- Bugfix: Restored ability to send duplicate `/me` messages.
- Bugfix: Notifications for moderators about other moderators deleting messages can now be disabled.
- Bugfix: Moderation mode and active filters are now preserved when opening a split as a popup.
- Bugfix: Fixed a bug that caused all badge highlights to use the same color.
- Bugfix: Allow starting Streamlink from Chatterino when running as a Flatpak.
- Dev: Renamed CMake's build option `USE_SYSTEM_QT5KEYCHAIN` to `USE_SYSTEM_QTKEYCHAIN`.
- Dev: Add benchmarks that can be compiled with the `BUILD_BENCHMARKS` CMake flag. Off by default.
</releaseNotes>
